## derived conclusion
Layer::PC is serialized as a vector of 32-byte Ristretto points only; validate_cipher_structure enforces PC.size == slots for base layers and forbids PC on PROD layers.
The public cipher artifact contains 44 PC point commitments across 22 wrapped base-layer ciphers, but no ComOpen/value/blind structures or native proof openings are serialized in secret.ct.
commit_ct hashes PC points and R_com into a public transcript commitment; it does not reveal openings. recrypt_com.hpp has ComOpen(value, blind), but those fields are local witness/opening material and are absent from public artifact serialization.
